reporting: Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Netherlands
description: Médecins du Monde requests support in two ongoing projects: 1) Supporting the Plateforme Migration Algérie; and 2) Access and rights to sexual and reproductive health of women in Oran. (also known as “Jardin des Femmes”) These projects are especially relevant to the embassy as they support two prioritized objectives: that of improving migration management and of stimulating social progress (strengthening civil society). To be more precise: through the first part of the project members of the migratory platform of Algeria (in the cities of Algiers and Oran) will be trained in assisting and protecting migrants living in Algeria Through the second part of the project, a selected number of civil society actors will be supported in their effort to reduce the sanitary risks related to sexual practices for both the Algerian and migrant population.

reporting: Gavi, The Vaccine Alliance
description: Targeted country assistance (TCA) are resources provided to in-country partners under Gavi’s partners’ engagement framework (PEF). A country’s TCA plan is based on needs expressed by the country during the joint appraisal discussions. It includes sets of activities, milestones and budget for a given year.Technical assistance is non-financial support provided by specialists. It can take the form of sharing information and expertise, training and consulting services.\n\nThe technical assistance provided through PEF is called targeted country assistance (TCA). This type of support mainly consists of staff permanently based in partners’ country offices. It is based on the demand and needs identified by the countries themselves.

reporting: Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Netherlands
description: The main goal of the project for migrants In Algiers Is to im­prove the access to care In general for the most vulnerable mi­grants In Algeria and to Improve the access to psychosoclal care In specific for migrants that are victims of violence and abuse. This will be achieved by providing emergency accommodation to migrants and by strengthening the links between them and several aid organizations. The desired results are that vulnerable migrant women and children are able to receive support adapted to their situation and that migrants In Algeria have access to the care they need. They will be supported In restoring the control over their lives.The organization, Caritas Alger, provided objectively verifiable indicators that can prove the achievement of the desired re­sults.

reporting: Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Netherlands
description: Doelstelling is het faciliteren van geslaagde vrijwillige terugkeer van sub-Sahara migranten uit Algerije naar landen van herkomst, en secundaire integratie in de maatschappij aldaar. In Algerije is het vrijwel onmogelijk de status van vluchteling, en de daarbij horende opvang, te verkrijgen. Daardoor leven veel asielzoekers onder erbarmelijke omstandigheden en willen terug naar hun land van herkomst.In het kort streeft de organisatie ernaar in de leefomstandigheden van asielzoekers te verbeteren en hen te helpen bij het terugkeren naar hun land van herkomst. Dit wordt gedaan d.m.v. counseling van migranten, medische hulp, onderwijs voor kinderen, ju ridische bijstand en hulp bij vrijwillige terugkeer en herintegratie van in Algerije gestrande migranten uit Sub-Sahara landen.

reporting: Federal Ministry for Economic Cooperation and Development (BMZ)
description: Die COVID-19-Pandemie in Algerien hat große negative gesundheitliche Folgen, welche sich in besonderem Maße auf arme Bevölkerungsgruppen auswirken. Die mit Verlauf der Pandemie stetig gestiegenen Infektionszahlen stellen das algerische Gesundheitssystem vor große Herausforderungen. Zudem befindet sich Algerien in einer Wirtschaftskrise, da der weltweite Rückgang der Ölpreise, der durch die Auswirkungen der COVID-19-Pandemie noch verstärkt wurde, zu einem Rückgang der Staatseinnahmen und des fiskalpolitischen Spielraums geführt hat. Œ ŒDas Vorhaben unterstützt Algerien bei der Bekämpfung der COVID-19-Pandemie und bei der Abmilderung der Auswirkungen der Pandemie auf die Gesamtbevölkerung inklusive vulnerabler Bevölkerungsteile. Im Rahmen des Vorhabens wird die Beschaffung von dringend benötigten medizinischen Produkten und Geräten für Krankenhäuser und Labore, einschließlich von Geräten für die Qualitätskontrolle von medizinischen Produkten finanziert. Zu den medizinischen Produkten und Geräten, die für Krankenhäuser bereitgestellt werden sollen, gehören biochemische Reagenzien, MRT-Geräte, Anlagen zur Sauerstoffproduktion, mobile Kliniken und Kühlkettenausrüstung. Die Ausrüstung für Labore zur Unterstützung der pharmazeutischen Qualitätskontrolle von Impfstoffen und Medikamenten umfasst u.a. Kühlräume für die Sterilitätskontrolle von Impfstoffen und Medikamenten. Des Weiteren werden die Fähigkeiten von Fachkräften im Gesundheitswesen zur Bewältigung der COVID-19-Pandemie durch Schulungen gestärkt.

reporting: Gavi, The Vaccine Alliance
description: Gavi with Alliance partners UNICEF and WHO is coordinating the development and implementation of AMC COVAX, the financing instrument that will support the participation of 92 lower-middle and low-income economies in the COVAX facility. The COVAX AMC is critical to ensure equitable access to COVID-19 vaccines, regardless of the income level of beneficiaries. This activity includes the infrastructure and technical support necessary to make sure COVID-19 vaccines can be safely delivered to all those who need them. Gavi is also part of the health systems work of the ACT-Accelerator effort, focusing on areas where it has expertise and experience, such as cold chain.

reporting: African Development Bank
description: The Project to Support the Development of Small and Medium sized Enterprises (PAD-SMES) is part of the strengthening of policies and tools for the promotion of SMEs in Algeria. It is intended to improve the supporting measures to promote SMEs development, and strengthen the dialogue between the public and private sectors. The planned intervention of this project is to assist the three (3) main national structures in charge of the SMEs promotion, coaching and follow-up in the strengthening of their capacities. The three agencies concerned are: The General Administration Office of SMEs (DGPME), the National Agency for the Development of SMEs (ANDPME) and the National Advisory Council for the Promotion of SMEs (CNCPME).

reporting: International Organization for Migration (IOM)
description: The project is contributing to the efforts of the Algerian Government to coordinate anti-trafficking responses, identify and prevent trafficking, prosecute traffickers, and protect and assist victims of trafficking through enhanced coordination, capacity building and awareness raising.

reporting: International Organization for Migration (IOM)
description: The project aims to assist children and young migrants with health assistance and assisted voluntary return and reintegration. It thus aims to improve access to necessary health care and awareness-raising activities on health risks and communicable diseases. The project also consists of the provision of services to support safe return for these migrants through active screening, Best Interest Assessment/Best Interest Determination for children, coordination with embassies, and pre-departure assistance.

reporting: International Organization for Migration (IOM)
description: Over the last few years, there has been an increase in the number of Algerian nationals leaving the country irregularly by sea, trying to reach Europe. IOM will implement a project to contribute to promoting safe and regular migration among Algerian nationals that are prone to migrate. To achieve this objective, IOM will make use of social media and digital communication with a Communication for Development (C4D) approach. This will start from an understanding of the context and people’s knowledge, attitudes and practices, to then tackle issues by developing empowering messaging tools, rolling out a targeted communication campaign and evaluating its results. The project will contribute to help migrants make informed choices on safe migration through a participatory process, where digital communication is used to support sustainable social and behavioral change.

reporting: Netherlands Enterprise Agency
description: The main goal of this cooperation project is to improve the quality of the phytosanitary control system in Algeria and to improve trade conditions in phyto-material between the two countries.

reporting: International Organization for Migration (IOM)
description: In order to assist migrants stranded in southern Algeria, IOM will undertake a series of complementary actions. IOM will engage with local stakeholders to raise awareness on assisted voluntary return and reintegration and increase referrals, provide migrants with information on assisted voluntary return and reintegration, through counselling and information sessions, provide direct assistance (shelter, food, medical assistance) to the most vulnerable beneficiaries and assist migrants with assisted voluntary return and reintegration.

reporting: Netherlands Enterprise Agency
description: This project envisions to support the ecosystem for entrepreneurs in Algeria, through building capacity at three Algerian Universities in the field of entrepreneurship. The project will help the university of Constantine and two universities in Oran individually to integrate entrepreneurship in their strategy and practices, in order to stimulate more students to start their own business. Interventions could focus on teaching methods, pre- or extracurricular activities, student-led events, strategy review or other forms of support.To make the capacity building tailor-made and context specific for every university, the project will start with a needs assessment which will lead to a concrete implementation plan for each of them.

reporting: Netherlands Enterprise Agency
description: With this project, the Orange Corners incubation programme in Algeria will be developed. This will strengthen the startup infrastructure in the country by offering an incubation programme in Algiers for 120 young social entrepreneurs over the course of three years, which will enable them to create new innovative businesses and social enterprises. At least 50% of these social entrepreneurs will be women, thereby supporting equal opportunities for women.

reporting: Netherlands Enterprise Agency
description: Through this project, a law firm is hired to provide advice on the construction of a legal entity for Orange Corners Algeria, to develop a charter and partnership agreements, to advise on the trademark registration and to execute this registration.

reporting: Netherlands Enterprise Agency
description: The purpose of this project is to provide aspiring entrepreneurs from Algeria with a practical, realistic, step-by-step guide on the process of starting a business. The process is now unclear, and there is a discrepancy between the theory of starting a business, and the reality of it. Service provider Sylabs, in collaboration with students from a University in Algiers will write and publish such a guide. The guide will contain a step-by-step guide, an overview of rules and regulations, tips and tricks from experts and young entrepreneurs themselves, identified blockages and recommendations.

reporting: Netherlands Enterprise Agency
description: This project enables RVO to design and implement more gender-sensitive PSD interventions. Having a gender specialist with a PSD background “on call” the PSD Toolkit interventions will provide insight into the opportunities PSD Coaches have to make their project more gender inclusive (becoming alert of our own blind spots).
